headline: DAT: Spot truckload volumes declined, rates fell sharply in February
summary: BEAVERTON, Ore., March 13, 2025--Spot truckload freight volumes settled lower in February, driven by a mix of seasonal slowing, winter weather, and shipper concerns about tariffs and economic volatility, said DAT Freight & Analytics, which operates the DAT One freight marketplace and DAT iQ data analytics service.
